2.body: This guide is aimed at both developers working on Rust programs for end-users and libraries developers. It focuses on currently available tooling for the Rust ecosystem, but also mentions more general advice or tooling. It has a hands-on focus and tries to provide actionnable items whenever possible. It will also mention the current limitations and missing parts. It builds upon existing resources, like llogiq's blog post .
2.title: About this guide
